Swarm Implementation:

Installa docker 

ubuntu@ip-172-31-25-201:~$ docker swarm init 
Swarm initialized: current node (m5p29t7sqajxglon2rasejnhx) is now a manager.

To add a worker to this swarm, run the following command:

    docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-2ztrlfli1cfmvlwqt6y8urtxrhqee8k7djd4y0uij1r0amtavs-9b8dj1pcnhs1rpdr6c1x677l5 172.31.25.201:2377

To add a manager to this swarm, run 'docker swarm join-token manager' and follow the instructions.

ubuntu@ip-172-31-25-201:~$ docker swarm join-token manager : it will give you a Manager token 
To add a manager to this swarm, run the following command:

    docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-2ztrlfli1cfmvlwqt6y8urtxrhqee8k7djd4y0uij1r0amtavs-64jw7r53ukdgtv96n074me6qx 172.31.25.201:2377

ubuntu@ip-172-31-25-201:~$ 

ubuntu@ip-172-31-25-201:~$ docker swarm join-token worker 	: It will give you a worker token


Lab-3

Manager + Worker Commands:

# Manager
$ docker swarm init - -advertise-addr <host-ip>		: initialise the swarm
$ docker service ls								: list services
$ docker service ps <name-of-service>			: list task of services
$ docker service create <name-of-service> <image-name>	: create new services
$ docker service rm <name-of-service>			: to remove the service
$ docker service scale <name-of-service>=5		: scale services
$ docker swarm leave							: leave the swarm 
Node left the swarm.
$ docker node rm rpy0k86k6s7jy1jcmwqxl8n98		: remove the node completely
rpy0k86k6s7jy1jcmwqxl8n98

# Worker Commands
Google it

Important:
Dockerfile -> Docker Image -> Docker Container -> Executing Docker Services 
